This PR lints various D3 modules.

Other than basic linting, in **d3-collection** and **d3-interpolate** a small number of uses of `Object` for typing arguments has been changed to use `any`. This was done as the use of `Object` causes a linting error, and the actual intended use of `object` as a proper type is not supported below TS 2.2.
`TODO` comments have been added in all these code locations to change to `object` when formally restricting the definitions for use with TS 2.2+. Currently, they are meant to remain backwards compatible.
